Charlize Theron attends the 23rd Annual Hollywood Film Awards at The Beverly Hilton Hotel on November 03, 2019 in Beverly Hills, California. JOHANNESBURG - Actress Charlize Theron was honoured with the Hollywood Career Achievement Award at the Hollywood Film Awards. Theron was honoured by Nicole Kidman at the prestigious awards ceremony held at the Beverly Hilton Hotel on Sunday. READ: Charlize Theron shows Springboks some love In a post on Instagram, the 44-year-old said she cried when Kidman described her as one of her heroes. "Still bawling my eyes out from when @nicolekidman called me one of her heroes while presenting me with the @hollywoodawards Career Achievement Award. Thank you #HollywoodAwards for this incredible honor, and thank you Nic for consistently showing up and being such an amazing friend", said Theron. Still bawling my eyes out from when @nicolekidman called me one of her heroes while presenting me with the @hollywoodawards Career Achievement Award. Thank you #HollywoodAwards for this incredible honor, and thank you Nic for consistently showing up and being such an amazing friend ❤️ I’ll go back to crying now A post shared by  Charlize Theron (@charlizeafrica) on Nov 4, 2019 at 12:54pm PST